{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/translate!/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Daisy Wang","author":"Daisy Wang"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"9210ce61-c996-55cc-95d0-cc0ff74c6f31","excerpt":"What is this? Translate! is an organisation that I founded to connect volunteer translators with charity organisations. Translate! utilises a web-based platform…","html":"<h3>What is this?</h3>\n<p>Translate! is an organisation that I founded to <strong>connect volunteer translators with charity organisations</strong>. Translate! utilises a <strong>web-based platform</strong> where charities can post requests for translations, and volunteers can sigh up to accept these translation requests. This project was inspired by the fact that Hong Kong has a vast bilingual population who are capable of serving as translators, and serve as a hugely under-utilised resource.Through this, we hope to increase the spread of a charity’s message, as well as free up more time for charities to engage in other tasks.</p>\n<p>We were funded from 2019-2020 by Kids4Kids through their Act!on for Change program, through which we received a <strong>3000 HKD grant</strong>.</p>\n<p>At the moment, we have partnered with Kids4Kids where we have helped translate <strong>10 children’s stories</strong> for their annual publication, the Treasury.</p>\n<h3>How does it work?</h3>\n<p>Translate! was build upon WordPress using the WP Job Manager plugin, and a modified version of the Robojobs theme.  In order to ensure quality, charities and volunteers must be verified before they can fully interact with the website. Charities post a request, and volunteers can browse through the postings to find opportunities of their liking, and respond accordingly.</p>\n<h3>The team behind it</h3>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/e95b5/team%20photo.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1024px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/51a8e/team%20photo.webp 340w,\n/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/713b7/team%20photo.webp 680w,\n/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/701c5/team%20photo.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/2e524/team%20photo.jpg 340w,\n/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/d330d/team%20photo.jpg 680w,\n/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/e95b5/team%20photo.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/e95b5/team%20photo.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Team Photo\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/7513f620be111e36aa353806c99a5d08/e95b5/team%20photo.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nI was fortunate enough to be able to collaborate with Clarisse Tsang, Coco Yeung, and Dionne Yeung on this project.</p>\n<h3>Where’s the website?</h3>\n<p>Unfortunately, due to all of the co-founders becoming increasingly busy with school, we have decided to end this project. We used to be at <a href=\"http://translate4good.com\">http://translate4good.com</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Translate!","date":"February 02, 2020","description":"A web app I co-founded that aimed to connect volunteer translators with charities.","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.207792207792208,"src":"/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/40a76/front_page.png","srcSet":"/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/c972b/front_page.png 340w,\n/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/27625/front_page.png 680w,\n/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/40a76/front_page.png 1360w,\n/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/1e49b/front_page.png 2040w,\n/static/461b47e6362706d7cd62eb29bc8414d3/cb65b/front_page.png 2558w","sizes":"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/translate!/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/room-to-read/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ISF Room to Read Chapter"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/horse/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Equine Gut Microbiome Research"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"]}